Pork available now! Look at that red color - this is exceptional pork - this is nutrient and flavor rich truly pasture raised pork. Outstanding from top-to-bottom - born-on-pasture, raised 100% outdoors, moved weekly through diverse green paddocks, no chemicals or pharmaceuticals, slow-grown for 10 months, processed at a local craft butcher. The final product reflects the wholesome life of these pigs. The pork is exceptionally delicious - sweet, melty and tender. It is rich in pasture-raised nutrition and omega-3 fats. It is true ethical and integrity meat, raised by us at Farmcraft to grace the table of you and your family. Link in bio to shop now. #pasturedpork #farmcraft

Hay is for pigs. #pigs #farmcraft During winter in Wisconsin, we don't have the beautiful sward of clover and soft grass for our pigs to eat. So we bring last summer's abundance to them - high quality alfalfa and clover hay for eating and stemmy hay for bedding.
